{"title_page": "Pain (Surname)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Surname|name=Pain|variant=Pyne, Paine|derivation=|language=[[Odia language|Odiya]], [[Bengali language|Bengali]]|origin=[[South Asia]]|languageorigin=[[Sanskrit language|Sanskrit]]|seealso=[[Satapathy]], [[Pathak]], [[Mishra]]}}\n\n'''Pain''' (Bengali: \u09aa\u09be\u0987\u09a8) is an Indian surname, found among [[Utkala Brahmin|Utkala Brahmins]] of [[Odisha]]. Alternative spellings include Paine and Pyne. \n\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ubrahmin.blogspot.com/2015/04/utkal-brahman-utkal-means-who-are-best.html?m=1|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n== About Pain Surname ==\nPain (Hindi:\u092a\u093e\u0907\u0928 )( Bengali:\u09aa\u09be\u0987\u09a8 )(Odia-) is a surname of [[Utkala Brahmin|Utkal Brahmin]] mostly found in  [[Odissa]], [[West Bengal]] and rarely found in other parts of India and abroad. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wikivisually.com/wiki/Utkala_Brahmin|title=Utkala Brahmin|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>They are honest, pious and noble Brahmins. They give more importance to the service of God, temple worship. Some of them act as priests. Some of them are engaged in business & agriculture and other professions. They are the highly revered community and devoted to God [[Jagannath|Jagganath]].\n\n==Origin of Pain Surname==\nThere are the different opinion among Utkal Brahmins about the origin of Pain surname alternative spelling Pyne and Paine, so it is very difficult to explain about the origin of Pain surname, however, according to a commonly accepted opinion the words Pain is likely to be derived from word Paniyari. Utkal Brahmins priests who offer or have offered paan to Lord Jagannath during Seva puja of God [[Jagannath|Jagganath]] is called Paniyari.\n\nPaniyari is a section of  Sevayata (priest) of the Utkal Brahmin community of India. They are honest, pious and noble Brahmins. The Utkal Brahmins Pyne are those who walk on the Path of Purity, truth, justice, goodness. They are the highly revered community and devoted to God. It is relevant to mention here Pyne is neither caste nor a family. It is only a title. According to another, less accepted opinion the words Pain is likely to be derived from word Pani.\n\n==Notable Person==\n* [[Ganesh Pyne]] Artist\n*[[Bedabrata Pain]] Film Maker\n\n==Reference==\n<references />\n[[Category:Hindu surnames]]\n[[Category:Surnames]]\n[[Category:Social groups of Odisha]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Surname|name=Pain|variant=Pyne, Paine|derivation=|language=[[Odia language|Odiya]], [[Bengali language|Bengali]]|origin=[[South Asia]]|languageorigin=[[Sanskrit language|Sanskrit]]|seealso=[[Satapathy]], [[Pathak]], [[Mishra]]}}\n\n'''Pain''' (Bengali: \u09aa\u09be\u0987\u09a8) is an Indian surname, found among [[Utkala Brahmin|Utkala Brahmins]] of [[Odisha]]. Alternative spellings include Paine and Pyne. \n\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ubrahmin.blogspot.com/2015/04/utkal-brahman-utkal-means-who-are-best.html?m=1|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n== About Pain Surname ==\nPain (Hindi:\u092a\u093e\u0907\u0928 )( Bengali:\u09aa\u09be\u0987\u09a8 )(Odia-) is a surname of [[Utkala Brahmin|Utkal Brahmin]] mostly found in  [[Odissa]], [[West Bengal]] and rarely found in other parts of India and abroad. They are honest, pious and noble Brahmins. They give more importance to the service of God, temple worship. Some of them act as priests. Some of them are engaged in business & agriculture and other professions. They are the highly revered community and devoted to God [[Jagannath|Jagganath]].\n\n==Origin of Pain Surname==\nThere are the different opinion among Utkal Brahmins about the origin of Pain surname alternative spelling Pyne and Paine, so it is very difficult to explain about the origin of Pain surname, however, according to a commonly accepted opinion the words Pain is likely to be derived from word Paniyari. Utkal Brahmins priests who offer or have offered paan to Lord Jagannath during Seva puja of God [[Jagannath|Jagganath]] is called Paniyari.\n\nPaniyari is a section of  Sevayata (priest) of the Utkal Brahmin community of India. They are honest, pious and noble Brahmins. The Utkal Brahmins Pyne are those who walk on the Path of Purity, truth, justice, goodness. They are the highly revered community and devoted to God. It is relevant to mention here Pyne is neither caste nor a family. It is only a title. According to another, less accepted opinion the words Pain is likely to be derived from word Pani.\n\n==Notable Person==\n* [[Ganesh Pyne]] Artist\n*[[Bedabrata Pain]] Film Maker\n\n==Reference==\n<references />\n[[Category:Hindu surnames]]\n[[Category:Surnames]]\n[[Category:Social groups of Odisha]]\n", "name_user": "Koushik Pain", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pain_(Surname)"}
